<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Electrolux is the Swedish-engineered side of a kitchen most LA owners don't realize is half European.</h2>

    <p>Electrolux AB has been making appliances out of Stockholm since 1919 — the parent corporation also owns Frigidaire (the North American mass-market brand) and AEG (the European sister brand). The Electrolux-branded products sold in the US sit at the premium end of the parent's portfolio — positioned above Frigidaire on the same showroom floor, below Miele and Bosch on the luxury side. In our 5-county SoCal service area, Electrolux shows up in a specific pattern: kitchen remodels from roughly 2014 onward where the homeowner wanted European engineering aesthetic at a price point below Miele, condos with builder-spec upgrade packages from the same era, and Westside rental properties whose landlords furnished kitchens with the EFLS / EI23 / EI30 combination because the Electrolux name carries premium connotation without the Miele price tag.</p>

    <p>Two Electrolux-specific service realities shape how we approach every call. First, the <strong>Electrolux / Frigidaire parts cross-compatibility</strong> matters more than most homeowners realize. Same Swedish parent, same engineering platforms across many US models — the door boot seal that fits an Electrolux EFLS627UTT often fits a Frigidaire equivalent, the drain pump that fits an EI23BC32SS often fits the corresponding Frigidaire French door, the bake element on an EI30 range often fits Frigidaire's matching size class. Our techs check both parts catalogs on every service call because Frigidaire-branded OEM parts often ship faster from LA-area distribution and fit physically identical. Second, the <strong>Perfect Steam drum boot seal failure pattern on 2017-2021 EFLS-series washers</strong> is the most consistent Electrolux service call in our LA mix — same year-window, same lower-lip tear, same fix every time. Knowing the pattern means we walk in with the part on the truck instead of ordering after diagnosis.</p>

    <p>This page covers Electrolux repair across all major appliance categories. Every Electrolux service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Electrolux or cross-compatible Frigidaire parts depending on supply, and an honest quote in writing before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 WASHER & DRYER -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Electrolux washer & dryer repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">EFLS, EFME, ECWM — the Perfect Steam laundry tier.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Electrolux laundry is where Electrolux's US service volume concentrates. Front-load washers (EFLS, EFLW), gas and electric dryers (EFME, EFMG), and the compact stackable ECWM line for small-space kitchens and ADUs. Perfect Steam is the Electrolux washer headline feature — pre-treats stains with steam injection at the start of the wash cycle.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>The 2017-2021 EFLS door boot seal pattern (most common Electrolux service call in LA)</h3>
      <p>EFLS627UTT, EFLS617SIW, and the surrounding EFLS-series production years between roughly 2017 and 2021 develop a consistent door boot seal failure around year 4 to 6 — the rubber boot's lower lip tears where drum splash sits against the seal during high-RPM spin. Symptoms our techs hear from homeowners: water on the laundry-room floor after a wash, mildew smell around the door area, sometimes an E-code related to overflow detection. Replacement is the fix; we carry OEM Electrolux boots on the truck for the common frame dimensions. <strong>$285-$425 typical, same-day.</strong> If your EFLS is in that 2017-2021 window and you've started seeing puddles, this is almost certainly the cause.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the door boot pattern, Electrolux washer service tree is conventional. Most-common service items by year-window:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> drain pump filter clog. Debris (coins, hair, lint) in the front-bottom filter compartment — sometimes a 10-minute no-parts fix. About 30% of "won't drain" calls resolve here.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 4-6:</strong> door boot seal (above), water inlet valve, drain pump failure. $185-$385 range.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6-8:</strong> Perfect Steam generator. The steam-injection module fails on units that ran heavy steam-cycle use. Replacement $385-$580.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-10:</strong> shock absorber wear, bearing seal degradation. Front bearing + drum seal as a paired set ($585-$880) extends machine life to year 14-16. Replacing bearing only without the seal will fail again within months.</li>
      <li><strong>Compact ECWM stackable:</strong> walking-into-spin issues at year 6-8 usually trace to suspension spring kit wear ($245-$385). Smaller chassis means tighter tolerance — minor wear shows up earlier than full-size machines.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Electrolux dryer service is less brand-specific. Most calls trace to thermal fuse blown from vent run blockage (always inspect the full vent path before replacing the fuse — fuse alone will blow again within weeks), heating element burnout at year 8-12, and idler pulley plus drum belt wear at year 7-10. Gas EFMG dryers add the gas valve coil failure mode around year 9-12. The dryer chassis on most EFME / EFMG units is engineered alongside the matching washer — service access patterns are similar, and the parts ecosystem overlaps cleanly with Frigidaire's matching tier.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REFRIGERATOR -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Electrolux refrigerator repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">EI23, EW23, EI28, EW28 — French door and Side-by-Side with PureAdvantage filtration.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Electrolux refrigerators in the US lineup cluster around two configurations: counter-depth French door (EI23 / EW23 in the 22-23 cu ft band) and Side-by-Side (EI28 / EW28 in the 26-28 cu ft band). PureAdvantage is Electrolux's water filtration system — a cartridge-based filter that handles the ice maker and door-mounted water dispenser. Functional design, but LA's hard water creates an Electrolux-specific service pattern worth knowing.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>PureAdvantage filter clogging is faster in WeHo / Beverly Hills / SGV than the manual implies</h3>
      <p>The PureAdvantage cartridge has a published 6-month replacement interval. In LA neighborhoods served by the San Gabriel Valley Municipal Water District (SGVMWD basin — San Marino, Arcadia, Pasadena foothills) or by the harder fractions of the LADWP supply (Beverly Hills, West Hollywood, Hancock Park, parts of the Westside), the filter clogs measurably faster — 3 to 4 months typical rather than 6. Symptoms when filter is overdue: ice production drops to nothing, water dispenser slows to a trickle, internal pressure rises against the inlet valve. Homeowners who follow the 6-month interval often end up replacing both the filter and the water inlet valve at year 3 to 4 because the back-pressure killed the valve. We catch this on diagnostic and tell you the LA-specific interval that actually applies to your address — not the boilerplate manual number.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the filtration story, Electrolux refrigerator service tree is mostly conventional. Most-common service items by year:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> ice maker assembly failure — flake formation, motor failure, or water line freeze-up in the door-mounted unit. Replacement assembly $245-$385. Water inlet valve replacement often paired ($185-$285).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-8:</strong> evaporator fan motor (freezer compartment fan — failure presents as freezer fine / fresh-food side warm), condenser fan motor, defrost timer or heater on units that haven't shifted to modern adaptive defrost. $245-$385 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7-10:</strong> condenser coil fouling on under-unit configurations (LA homes with pet hair compound this faster), main control board, door gasket compression on heavily-used units.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> compressor work, sealed-system refrigerant leaks. At this age we walk you through repair-vs-replace economics carefully — a compressor swap runs $580-$880, and on a 12-year-old Electrolux that's approaching new-unit territory. We tell you the math honestly before parts get ordered.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Side-by-Side EI28 and EW28 units add the dispenser-tower assembly to the failure tree (ice chute door, dispenser actuator, dispenser control panel) — typical service year 6 to 9 on heavy-use households. The EI23 and EW23 French door configurations are mechanically closer to the surrounding Frigidaire French door tier than to the Side-by-Side variants, which means parts cross-compatibility is strongest here.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 RANGE & OTHER -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, Electrolux ranges, ovens, dishwashers, microwaves</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">PreciseAir convection, IQ-Touch controls, EIDW dishwashers.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Outside laundry and refrigeration, Electrolux's US lineup covers ranges, wall ovens, dishwashers, and over-the-range microwaves. PreciseAir is Electrolux's convection system — a directional-airflow configuration that bakes more evenly than conventional convection but adds calibration sensitivity over time.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Ranges (EI30, EW30, EI36)</h3>
        <p>Electric (EI30) and dual-fuel (EW30) freestanding ranges; the EI36 wider unit appears in higher-spec kitchens. PreciseAir convection on premium tier. Most common service: oven temperature sensor / thermostat drift causing PreciseAir to bake unevenly ($145-$215), convection fan motor at year 7-10 ($285-$425), surface element or igniter ($145-$215). The PreciseAir directional vent occasionally needs recalibration after element replacement — not a part, just a configuration step that competitors who just "replace the element" skip.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Wall ovens (EI30, EW30 series)</h3>
        <p>Single and double wall oven configurations. IQ-Touch glass control panel on premium tier. Service items: bake/broil element, oven temperature sensor, control board, door hinge alignment (heavy steel door wears the hinge over years). <a href="/brands/electrolux-wall-oven-repair/">Electrolux wall oven repair page →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Dishwashers (EIDW, EI24ID)</h3>
        <p>Mid-tier integrated dishwashers with stainless tubs. Service tree: drain pump ($245-$385), water inlet valve ($185-$285), control board ($345-$525), door latch / interlock. The EIDW series shares chassis architecture with Frigidaire Gallery dishwashers — parts cross-compatibility helps with same-day completion. <a href="/brands/electrolux-dishwasher-repair/">Electrolux dishwasher repair page →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Microwaves (over-the-range)</h3>
        <p>OTR microwaves matched to the Electrolux range and wall oven aesthetic. Common service items: door switch, magnetron, turntable motor. Less brand-specific than the range or refrigerator service trees — Electrolux microwaves share OEM components with multiple parent-brand variants.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Electrolux Professional (commercial dishwasher)</h3>
        <p>Note that Electrolux also runs a separate commercial line under "Electrolux Professional" — under-counter and hood-type warewashing for restaurant kitchens. Different parts chain, different pricing ($120 commercial diagnostic), different service approach. <a href="/brands/electrolux-professional-dishwasher-repair/">Electrolux Professional dishwasher repair →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Frigidaire cross-platform service</h3>
        <p>Worth knowing: if you have a Frigidaire appliance alongside your Electrolux, our techs can service both on the same dispatch — same parts catalog overlap, same diagnostic conventions, same parent-brand engineering platform. Roughly 40% of our Electrolux service calls also touch a Frigidaire appliance in the same household.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 FAILURE PATTERNS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05, Common Electrolux failure patterns</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we see on Electrolux service calls across SoCal.</h2>

    <p>Year-window pattern recognition matters on Electrolux because the failure curves are tight — same-spec units fail in similar ways at similar ages, which makes diagnosis faster and parts pre-staging more reliable. Patterns our techs encounter routinely:</p>

    <div class="error-table">
      <div class="error-row"><strong>EFLS door boot (year 4-6)</strong> — 2017-2021 production cohort. Lower lip tear from drum splash. Water on floor after wash. $285-$425.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>EFLS Perfect Steam (year 6-8)</strong> — Steam generator fails on heavy steam-cycle households. $385-$580.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>EI23 / EW23 ice maker (year 3-5)</strong> — Door-mounted assembly fails first; water valve usually paired. $245-$385.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>PureAdvantage filter back-pressure (year 3-4 in hard-water areas)</strong> — Filter overdue → valve damaged. Replace both. $185-$285.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>EI28 / EW28 dispenser tower (year 6-9)</strong> — Side-by-Side dispenser actuator or chute door. $245-$385.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>PreciseAir convection drift (year 7-10)</strong> — Temperature sensor + fan motor as paired service. $285-$425.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>EIDW drain pump (year 5-8)</strong> — Frigidaire-platform crossover; same pump fits both. $245-$385.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>ECWM compact suspension (year 6-8)</strong> — Walking-into-spin on stackables. Spring kit. $245-$385.</div>
    </div>

    <p>Reset procedure for any Electrolux appliance showing an error: kill the breaker for a full 10 minutes (Electrolux control boards hold latched faults like most modern appliances). About 15% of error codes clear at this step at no parts cost. If the code returns, that's the diagnostic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 MODELS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Models we service most often</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Electrolux model families in heavy SoCal service rotation.</h2>

    <p class="lead">A representative sample of Electrolux model families our techs service routinely. Not exhaustive — Electrolux's US catalog is broad and revs annually — but covers the units that show up most often on our route.</p>

    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Front-Load Washers</h3>
        <p class="model-list">EFLS627UTT · EFLS617SIW · EFLW417SIW · EFLW427UIW</p>
        <p>EFLS-series full-size front-loaders with Perfect Steam. 2017-2021 cohort is the door-boot-seal era. Service-tree-dominant in our LA mix.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Compact Stackable Washer/Dryer</h3>
        <p class="model-list">ECWM3CPS · ELFE7637AW · ELFE7437AT</p>
        <p>24-inch compact stackables. ADUs, small condos, urban kitchens. Suspension and bearing service heavier than full-size due to tighter tolerance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Dryers, Electric & Gas</h3>
        <p class="model-list">EFME627UTT · EFMG617SIW · EFME417SIW</p>
        <p>EFME = electric, EFMG = gas. Matched to EFLS washer chassis. Standard service tree — thermal fuse + vent inspection, heating element, idler pulley.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>French Door Refrigerators</h3>
        <p class="model-list">EI23BC32SS · EW23BC87SS · EI23BC68SS · EW23BC85KS</p>
        <p>Counter-depth French door, 22-23 cu ft. PureAdvantage filtration. Standard ice maker + condenser fan failures, hard-water filter pattern in WeHo / SGV.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
