<!-- 08 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Electrolux jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Electrolux service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Electrolux EFLS627UTT front-load washer, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Water on laundry-room floor after every wash cycle. Owner noticed mildew smell around the door area. Unit was 5 years old, in the 2019 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Door boot seal tear at the lower lip, classic 2017-2021 EFLS pattern. Confirmed by visual inspection — small radial tears at the 6-o'clock position where drum splash sits during high-RPM spin.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Door boot replacement with OEM Electrolux part (in stock on the truck). Reinstalled, ran test cycle, confirmed no leaks.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $355 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 90 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Electrolux EI23BC32SS French Door, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice production dropped to almost nothing over a 4-month window. Water dispenser slowed at the same time.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> PureAdvantage filter overdue — homeowner was following the 6-month manual interval, but the SGVMWD basin water in Pasadena clogs the filter in 3-4 months. Filter heavily restricted, back-pressure damaged the water inlet valve. Both needed replacement.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> New PureAdvantage cartridge installed, water inlet valve replaced with OEM part, lines flushed. Ice production restored within 24 hours. Recommended 4-month filter interval going forward.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $275 total. Same-day, 75 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Electrolux EI30EF45QS electric range, Newport Beach</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Oven baking unevenly — front of pan browning, back staying pale. Convection cycle made the issue worse, not better.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> PreciseAir convection fan motor running at reduced RPM (year 8 unit, bearing wear). Temperature sensor reading slightly off-spec but within tolerance. The fan was failing first; the sensor was secondary.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Convection fan motor replaced with OEM Electrolux part. Temperature sensor replaced as paired-service preventive (cheap part, same access). PreciseAir directional vent recalibrated after replacement. Verified even bake on test cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $445 total. Same-day, 2 hours on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Electrolux EW28BS85KS Side-by-Side, Calabasas</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Fresh-food side warming up to 48°F overnight. Freezer holding temp normally. Owner reported the issue started gradually over a week.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Evaporator fan motor in freezer compartment failed. Classic split-temperature presentation — freezer fine because the evap coil still holds cold, fresh-food side warming because no fan to circulate the cold air over to the upper side. Compressor running normally. Defrost system clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Evaporator fan motor replaced with OEM part. Confirmed normal airflow on test cycle. Fresh-food side pulled back to 38°F within 4 hours.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

